  "id": "BIT-envoy-2026-26310",
  "summary": "Crash for scoped ip address in Envoy during DNS",
  "details": "Envoy is a high-performance edge/middle/service proxy. Prior to 1.37.1, 1.36.5, 1.35.8, and 1.34.13, calling Utility::getAddressWithPort with a scoped IPv6 addresses causes a crash. This utility is called in the data plane from the original_src filter and the dns filter. This vulnerability is fixed in 1.37.1, 1.36.5, 1.35.8, and 1.34.13.",
